{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/data-visualization-of-fauna-species-in-brazils-federal-conservation-units-using-r-ac9e2ac66e4", "time": 1683008585.5168781, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/data-visualization-of-fauna-species-in-brazils-federal-conservation-units-using-r-ac9e2ac66e4/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Data Visualization of Fauna Species in Brazil\u2019s Federal Conservation Units using R | by Luis Eduardo La Torre | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Data Visualization of Fauna Species in Brazil\u2019s Federal Conservation Units using R", "description": "Welcome to my very first article in Data Science! I\u2019ll try to explain this work in an easy and straight to the point way. Federal Conservation Units (abbreviation \u201cUC\u201d) are protected areas of the\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "http://www.dados.gov.br/dataset/especies-da-fauna-em-unidades-de-conservacao", "anchor_text": "http: // www. data.gov.br/dataset/especies-da-fauna-em-unidades-de-conservacao", "paragraph_index": 4}], "all_paragraphs": ["Welcome to my very first article in Data Science! I\u2019ll try to explain this work in an easy and straight to the point way.", "Federal Conservation Units (abbreviation \u201cUC\u201d) are protected areas of the Brazilian national territory, delimited by the government, characterized by its relevance in natural characteristics, where the protection and preservation of biodiversity occurs.", "Biodiversity represents a whole set of life varieties of species present in the biosphere, in our environment, as well as their genes and the entire ecosystem that involves the relationships between species. Man, as an integral part of the land, belongs to this ecosystem and becomes responsible for its actions that may affect the environmental balance.", "Current times, in which occurs more and more unrestrained actions and activities by deed-falsifiers, big owners, illegal logging and poaching, show us how we should become more attentive and watchful.", "Thus, I came across a database of threatened and almost threatened fauna present in UCs, provided by ICMBio (Chico Mendes Institute for Biodiversity Conservation) and made available updated until 2018 at http: // www. data.gov.br/dataset/especies-da-fauna-em-unidades-de-conservacao. It is a .csv file with 13 instances containing: species name, class, order, family, vertebrate or not, UC (Conservation Unit), UF (Federation Unit), etc.", "So, I decided to perform a more accurate analysis and explore some other implicit relevant data in this dataset using some of the tools of the R language.", "My goal was to extract 3 information from the countless ones still possible but not specified directly in this dataset, they are:\u2022 UCs with a greater diversity of threatened and near-threatened fauna;\u2022 UCs with a greater diversity of threatened and near-threatened fauna in the Federal District (abbreviation \u201cDF\u201d);\u2022 Threatened and near-threatened species with occurrence in UCs in DF area.", "No more talk, get to work!", "At first, I imported the .csv with", "Converting to tibble so that data handling occurs in a more appropriate way", "Now we have a data.frame (df) from the .csv file.", "After a few more steps of data wrangling, the data.frame is now ready to discover the information.", "To count the number of times that each UC appears in the dataset, I regrouped into UC and UF, and rearranged it into another df called uc_ordem.", "Now, to better visualize the data and get the first information I wanted, I generated a word cloud with 50 UCs of greater frequency and a bar graph containing the 10 UCs with the greatest diversity of species at risk.", "According to the data contained in the dataset, the Biological Reserves of Marinha do Arvoredo and Sooterama, together with the Abrolhos National Park, are the UCs that have the greatest diversity of threatened and almost threatened species (48 species each).", "With this information already presented, it became easier to collect the last two informations proposed here at the beginning of this article. So, let\u2019s go!", "To filter only the DF UCs sorted by different number of species, I used the filter() function and then generated a bar graph of the new data.frame generated.", "ESEC of \u00c1guas Emendadas is the UC with the greatest distinction of endangered species within the Federal District area.", "As a last step in this exploratory analysis of data in R, in order to extract the last information I wanted, I created the data.frame animals_df from the unique() function, which allowed me to extract single elements that were repeated.", "Finally, I have 22 species names that features the Cerrado biome as one of their habitats.", "Now that I have introduced you to some of the many tools for data analysis included in the R language, I encourage you to get more information from the many contained in this dataset, and even other environmental datasets, obtaining new data and contributing using Data Science in order to preserve and save biodiversity .", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Engineer graduated at University of Bras\u00edlia (UnB) | Postgraduating in Data Science and also a nature enthusiast."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fac9e2ac66e4&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fdata-visualization-of-fauna-species-in-brazils-federal-conservation-units-using-r-ac9e2ac66e4&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fdata-visualization